%TUTORIAL --------------  IBM PC File Transfer Program  --------------T TUTORIAL
%OPTION ===>_ZCMD                                                              +

                            Options for SEND command

%LRECL(n)+ When you are%sending+a file, LRECL specifies the logical record
           length of the host file or dataset.  "n" is the number of characters
           in each record.

 If LRECL is omitted and:

 o You are creating a new file, a length of 80 is assumed.

 o Your are replacing an existing file or dataset, the length of the records in
   that file or dataset is assumed.

 If you are adding a file to the end of another file or to the end of a dataset
 (using the APPEND option), the value of LRECL for the existing file is assumed
 and you should not specify another value.

 (More on next panel - press%Enter+to continue)
)PROC
 &ZCONT = VPCT017
 &ZUP   = VPCT000
)END
